# Sister project — kalam-website

Kalam is split across two repos that share a single roadmap (`.doc/upgrade-plan.md`).

## Repo map

| Repo | Path | What it is |
|------|------|------------|
| **kalam** (this repo) | `C:\Users\alifa\Development\BalaHeadache Projects\kalam` | Tauri v2 desktop app — Svelte 4 frontend, Rust backend, open source (FSL) |
| **kalam-website** | `C:\Users\alifa\Development\BalaHeadache Projects\kalam-website` | SvelteKit on Cloudflare Workers — marketing site, user/admin dashboards, Stripe billing, license API, OpenAuth |

## How they connect

- The desktop app calls `GET /api/license/validate?key=KALAM-XXXX` on the website Worker to check Pro status.
- The desktop app may POST to `/api/analytics/ingest` for first-party telemetry.
- License keys are generated by the website (Stripe webhook → D1 → KV) and entered by users in the desktop app's Settings.
- `PlanStatus` (Free / Trial / Pro / Expired) lives in the desktop app's Rust config; the website is the source of truth for validity.

## When working in this repo

- Changes to license validation, plan gating, or telemetry may need a matching endpoint or schema change in **kalam-website**.
- The upgrade plan (`.doc/upgrade-plan.md`) is the canonical spec — refer to it for phase scope and feature gating details.
- Deferred tasks for this repo are in `.doc/To-Do.md`; website tasks are in `kalam-website/.doc/To-Do.md`.
